{"id":"math/0604326","submitter":"Francesco Russo","authors":"Fausto Gozzi, Francesco Russo (LAGA)","title":"Weak Dirichlet processes with a stochastic control perspective","comments":"22 pages. To appear: Stochastic Processes and Their Applications","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":"Preprint LAGA-Paris 13 2005-14","categories":"math.PR","license":null,"abstract":"  The motivation of this paper is to prove verification theorems for stochastic\noptimal control of finite dimensional diffusion processes without control in\nthe diffusion term, in the case that the value function is assumed to be\ncontinuous in time and once differentiable in the space variable ($C^{0,1}$)\ninstead of once differentiable in time and twice in space ($C^{1,2}$), like in\nthe classical results. For this purpose, the replacement tool of the It\\^{o}\nformula will be the Fukushima-Dirichlet decomposition for weak Dirichlet\nprocesses. Given a fixed filtration, a weak Dirichlet process is the sum of a\nlocal martingale $M$ plus an adapted process $A$ which is orthogonal, in the\nsense of covariation, to any continuous local martingale. The mentioned\ndecomposition states that a $C^{0,1}$ function of a weak Dirichlet process with\nfinite quadratic variation is again a weak Dirichlet process. That result is\nestablished in this paper and it is applied to the strong solution of a Cauchy\nproblem with final condition. Applications to the proof of verification\ntheorems will be addressed in a companion paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 14 Apr 2006 05:04:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
